# Roblox Luau Style

## Strings

- Prefer Roblox backtick interpolation.
- Do not introduce `string.format` when interpolation is enough.

```lua
local text = `{player.Name} dealt {damage} damage`
```

## Code shape

- Prefer direct, readable modules over unnecessary abstraction.
- Keep lifecycle and entry methods easy to find near the top of entry modules.
- Push pure logic into helper modules instead of growing entry files indefinitely.
- Follow the repository's existing file layout instead of forcing a new one.

## Consistency

- Match the naming and structure already used by the surrounding system.
- Reuse existing helpers and project conventions before adding new patterns.
